System Requirements :
---------------------

*) Ruby interpreter

*) Gtk Bindings for Ruby

	------------------------------------
	| Dependencies Install Instruction |
	------------------------------------

For Ubuntu/Debian GNU/Linux users,

	1) Open Terminal and install ruby and ruby-gtk2 using your package manager,
	
	$ sudo apt-get install ruby ruby-gtk2 

	2) Now extract the downloaded .zip from github repo and double click gpa.rb  

	Easy enough ?

For Window$ users,

	I don't know whether you could understand what I mean....

	1) Download and install Ruby ( http://rubyinstaller.org/downloads/ )

	2) Install Gtk+ Runtime ( http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/ruby-gnome2/ruby-gnome2-0.16.0-1-i386-mswin32.exe?download )

	3) Install gtk2 gem

	c:\ruby\bin\> gem install gtk2

	3) Run gpa.rb file 

	E:\gpacalc\> ruby gpa.rb

	If this don't work, ask Google :P


For Mac users,
	
	ask Google :P


